File: Valentine's Day red roses with ribbon. Pixabay/Adonyig BOGOTA - Valentine’s Day is coming and flower exports are in full swing. That's why workers at a flower company in Colombia are hard at work to make sure you’re gift-ready. Augusto Solano is the President of the Colombian Flowers Exporters Association. He says an estimated 650 million Colombian flowers will be sold to foreign markets. Of the millions of flowers, Solano says most of them are roses.